FBIS4-64567 "drweu087_h_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-087 Daily Report 3 May 1994 GERMANY Kohl, European Jewish Representatives Meet in Bonn Kohl, European Jewish Representatives Meet in Bonn AU0305151094 Berlin DIE WELT in German 3 May 94 p 2 AU0305151094 Berlin DIE WELT German BFN [Unattributed report: "Jewish Representatives Visit Kohl"] [Excerpt] Yesterday in Bonn, Chancellor Helmut Kohl and a European Jewish Congress delegation led by Congress Chairman Jean Kahn discussed measures to combat xenophobia and racism. The delegation expressed its great concern over the growing excesses in Germany. Kohl said the federation and laender were doing everything in their power to combat such activities. The chancellor added that on a European Union level, the German Government would call for the adoption of "common measures against extremism and xenophobia." Kohl and the delegation agreed that in this respect, particular attention should be paid to "the system of upbringing in all European countries." Ignatz Bubis, chairman of the Central Jewish Council in Germany, and Israel Singer, general secretary of the World Jewish Congress, also took part in the meeting.
